Ask HN: Recommend me a good 5G Mobile Router
text:
I will be moving offices shortly and have just discovered that there is no possibility Fibre To Building at the address and Fibre To Cabinet is limited to 20mb with little prospect of an upgrade any time soon. I currently have 76mb which is adequate but wouldn't want to suffer such a severe downgrade.

MY obvious fallback option is Starlink, which would be OK but for the premium subscription and set up cost.

This leaves me with a 4/5G mobile signal. I would, therefore, need to buy a suitable router to provide wi-fi and at least one ethernet port.

Any suggestions would be welcome?

Ask HN: How can engineers profit from tech recruitment
text:
How can an engineer capture some of the value from the tech recruitment market? It seems to me engineers are used as goods that are traded between people who don’t understand tech or the market. It's exploitative and opportunistic — how can a random person just show up in LinkedIn and start trading engineers and extract value from their major life choices?

Engineers understand the technology and market and would have a huge information advantage compared to someone with no experience in the field. Even just consulting on some domain/tech knowledge for recruiters would benefit the recruiters.

How can I, as an engineer, get some of that pie?
